<subSubSection pageId="271" pageNumber="876" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="271.[176,1384,1510,2332]" pageId="271" pageNumber="876">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,423,1551,1585]" pageId="271" pageNumber="876">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 203 mm, tail 223 mm, hindfoot 42 mm. Nospecific data are available for body weight. The Small-eared Rat is medium-sized, with relatively small ears. Pelage is long, with sparsely distributed, shortish black guard hairs. Dorsum is dark gray, speckled with ashy white, slightly browner on sides. Venter is dark buffy brown, sharply demarcated from dorsum. Feet and digits are brownish black. Ears are similar in color to dorsum. Tail is 110% of head-body length, blackish for basal one-half, and white for distal one-half. There are three pairs of mammae: one post-axillary and two inguinal. Skull has heavy rostrum, broad molars, short palatal openings, and very small bullae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
